<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="365" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1926,2025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1927,1953]" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="de Saint Laurent, 1973" authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[399,750,1926,1953]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Calliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[399,481,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">Calliax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Saint Laurent, M. de" box="[489,750,1926,1953]" firstAuthor="de Saint Laurent" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" pagination="513 - 516" refId="ref7875" refString="Saint Laurent, M. de (1973) Sur la systematique et la phylogenie des Thalassinidea: definition des familles des Callianassidae et des Upogebiidae et diagnose de cinq genres nouveaux (Crustacea Decapoda). Comptes Rendus Hebdomadaires de Seances de l'Academie des Sciences, Serie D, 277, 513 - 516." type="journal article" year="1973">de Saint Laurent, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, has rather a complex taxonomic history (Hyžný &amp; Gašparič 2014; Ngoc-Ho 2014). Here the concept of the genus presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ngoc-Ho" box="[895,1074,1963,1989]" firstAuthor="Ngoc-Ho" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" pagination="439 - 555" refId="ref7577" refString="Ngoc-Ho, N. (2003) European and Mediterranean Thalassinidea (Crustacea, Decapoda). Zoosystema, 25, 439 - 555." type="journal article" year="2003">Ngoc-Ho (2003</bibRefCitation>
, 2014) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Poore" box="[1203,1411,1962,1989]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Poore" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" pagination="73 - 146" refId="ref7719" refString="Poore, G. C. B., Dworschak, P. C. D., Robles, R., Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Felder, D. L. (2019) A new classification of Callianassidae and related families (Crustacea: Decapoda: Axiidea) derived from a molecular phylogeny with morphological support. Memoirs of Museum Victoria, 78, 73 - 146. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 2019.78.05" type="journal article" year="2019">
Poore 
<emphasis box="[1275,1323,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="364">et al</emphasis>
. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
is followed rather than that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai" box="[465,610,1998,2025]" firstAuthor="Sakai" pageId="1" pageNumber="364" pagination="1 - 520" refId="ref8062" refString="Sakai, K. (2011) Axioidea of the World and a Reconsideration of the Callianassoidea (Decapoda, Thalassinidea, Callianassida). Crustaceana Monographs, 13, 1 - 520. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789047424185" type="journal article" year="2011">Sakai (2011)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,153,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">
It has been argued that at least for some genera the morphology of the major P1 propodus can be diagnostic on the genus level (
<bibRefCitation author="Hyzny, M." box="[334,477,189,215]" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" pagination="49 - 64" refId="ref6253" refString="Hyzny, M. (2012) Calliaxina chalmasii (Brocchi, 1883) comb. nov. (Decapoda: Axiidea: Callianassidae: Eucalliacinae), a ghost shrimp from the Middle Miocene of Europe, with reappraisal of the fossil record of Eucalliacinae. Zootaxa, 3492, 49 - 64." type="journal article" year="2012">Hyžný 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hyzny &amp; Muller" box="[488,743,189,215]" firstAuthor="Hyzny" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" pagination="967 - 993" refId="ref6840" refString="Hyzny, M. &amp; Muller, P. M. (2012) The fossil record of Glypturus Stimpson, 1866 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Axiidea, Callianassidae) revisited, with notes on palaeoecology and palaeobiogeography. Palaeontology, 55, 967 - 993. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1475 - 4983.2012.01169. x" type="journal article" year="2012">Hyžný &amp; Müller 2012</bibRefCitation>
). In this respect, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[1046,1128,189,215]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Calliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1128,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">Calliax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identifiable based on the following characters (emended from Hyžný &amp; Gašparič 2014): 1) major propodus rectangular, usually longer than high; 2) fixed finger shorter than manus, with a (double) ridge accompanied by a furrow and/or depression extending onto manus; 3) fixed finger with subdistal tooth on the occlusal margin. It should be mentioned that the ridge is well-developed mainly in larger specimens, whereas in smaller individuals it is faint or not present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,153,503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">
Even more diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[492,574,369,395]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Calliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[492,574,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">Calliax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the morphology of the minor chela (Hyžný &amp; Gašparič 2014; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poore" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Poore" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" pagination="73 - 146" refId="ref7719" refString="Poore, G. C. B., Dworschak, P. C. D., Robles, R., Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Felder, D. L. (2019) A new classification of Callianassidae and related families (Crustacea: Decapoda: Axiidea) derived from a molecular phylogeny with morphological support. Memoirs of Museum Victoria, 78, 73 - 146. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 2019.78.05" type="journal article" year="2019">
Poore 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
), which, unfortunately, is not observable in the present material. In this respect, 
<bibRefCitation author="Poore" box="[1092,1355,405,432]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Poore" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" pagination="73 - 146" refId="ref7719" refString="Poore, G. C. B., Dworschak, P. C. D., Robles, R., Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Felder, D. L. (2019) A new classification of Callianassidae and related families (Crustacea: Decapoda: Axiidea) derived from a molecular phylogeny with morphological support. Memoirs of Museum Victoria, 78, 73 - 146. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j. mmv. 2019.78.05" type="journal article" year="2019">
Poore 
<emphasis box="[1164,1212,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">et al</emphasis>
. (2019: 126)
</bibRefCitation>
argued that: “the wide gap between the fingers of the minor cheliped, with an intermediate tooth, immediately defines species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[232,314,477,503]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Calliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="365" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[232,314,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="365">Calliax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.”
</paragraph>
